1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with fundamental limits of rate and reliability in MIMO communications, which is a core topic in information theory. 
2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the tradeoff between rate, reliability, and computational complexity in MIMO communications, which is relevant to the design and optimization of communication networks. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the optimization of encoder-decoder designs and policies, which is related to the control of communication systems. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the optimization of complexity and power in MIMO communications, which is relevant to the design and implementation of network protocols. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper's focus on optimizing encoder-decoder designs and policies may involve machine learning techniques, such as neural networks or reinforcement learning.
